<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Hash on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/hash/</link><description>Recent content in Hash on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/hash/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Python TypeError — Unhashable Type</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/callable-not-hashable/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/callable-not-hashable/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="typeerror--unhashable-type"&gt;TypeError — Unhashable Type&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;TypeError&lt;/code&gt; with the message &amp;ldquo;unhashable type: &amp;lsquo;X&amp;rsquo;&amp;rdquo; is raised when you try to use a mutable object (like a list, dict, or set) as a dictionary key or as a set element. Only hashable (immutable) objects can be used as dictionary keys or set members.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hashable objects have a &lt;code&gt;__hash__()&lt;/code&gt; method that returns a consistent integer value. Immutable types like &lt;code&gt;int&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;str&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;tuple&lt;/code&gt;, and &lt;code&gt;frozenset&lt;/code&gt; are hashable. Mutable types like &lt;code&gt;list&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;dict&lt;/code&gt;, and &lt;code&gt;set&lt;/code&gt; are not hashable because their contents can change, which would invalidate the hash.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Python TypeError: unhashable type — 'dict' / 'list' Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/typeerror-hashable/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/typeerror-hashable/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="typeerror-unhashable-type--dict--list"&gt;TypeError: unhashable type — &amp;lsquo;dict&amp;rsquo; / &amp;rsquo;list&amp;rsquo;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;TypeError&lt;/code&gt; with &lt;code&gt;unhashable type: 'dict'&lt;/code&gt; (or &lt;code&gt;'list'&lt;/code&gt;) is raised when you try to use a mutable container (dict, list, set) as a dictionary key or as an element of a set. Python requires hashable (immutable) types for keys and set members.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A hashable object must have a &lt;code&gt;__hash__()&lt;/code&gt; method that returns the same value for the object&amp;rsquo;s lifetime. Mutable types like &lt;code&gt;dict&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;list&lt;/code&gt;, and &lt;code&gt;set&lt;/code&gt; cannot be hashed because their content can change, which would invalidate the hash.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Ruby KeyError — Key Not Found Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/ruby/keyerror-ruby/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/ruby/keyerror-ruby/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="keyerror--key-not-found"&gt;KeyError — Key Not Found&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;KeyError&lt;/code&gt; is raised when you try to access a hash key that doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist using &lt;code&gt;fetch&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;Hash#key?&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ruby hashes raise &lt;code&gt;KeyError&lt;/code&gt; when you use &lt;code&gt;fetch&lt;/code&gt; to access a non-existent key. Unlike bracket notation (&lt;code&gt;[]&lt;/code&gt;), &lt;code&gt;fetch&lt;/code&gt; doesn&amp;rsquo;t return &lt;code&gt;nil&lt;/code&gt; by default — it raises an error.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common causes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Using fetch without default&lt;/strong&gt; — accessing a key that doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assuming key exists&lt;/strong&gt; — not checking if a key is present before access&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Typo in key name&lt;/strong&gt; — misspelling a key&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Missing nested key&lt;/strong&gt; — accessing a deeply nested key that&amp;rsquo;s absent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 1: fetch without default value&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;config &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; { &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;host&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;localhost&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;config&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;fetch(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;port&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# KeyError: key not found: &amp;#34;port&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 2: Typo in key name&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;user &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; { &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;name&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Alice&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;email&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;alice@example.com&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;user&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;fetch(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;ename&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# KeyError: key not found: &amp;#34;ename&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 3: Missing nested key&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;data &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; { &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;user&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; { &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;name&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Alice&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; } }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;data&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;fetch(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;user&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;fetch(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;address&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# KeyError: key not found: &amp;#34;address&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 4: Integer vs String key confusion&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;hash &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; { &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;one&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;two&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;hash&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;fetch(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;1&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# KeyError: key not found: &amp;#34;1&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-use-fetch-with-default-value"&gt;Fix 1: Use fetch with default value&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Wrong&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;config&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;fetch(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;port&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# KeyError&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Correct&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;config&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;fetch(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;port&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;8080&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# 8080&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-bracket-notation-with-default"&gt;Fix 2: Use bracket notation with default&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Wrong&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;config&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;fetch(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;port&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# KeyError&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Correct&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;config&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;port&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;||&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;8080&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# 8080&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-dig-for-nested-access"&gt;Fix 3: Use dig for nested access&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Wrong&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;data&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;fetch(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;user&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;fetch(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;address&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# KeyError&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Correct&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;data&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;dig(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;user&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;address&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# nil (no error)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;data&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;dig(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;user&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;address&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;||&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;No address&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-check-key-existence-first"&gt;Fix 4: Check key existence first&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Wrong&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;value &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; hash&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;fetch(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;key&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# KeyError&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Correct&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; hash&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;key?(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;key&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; value &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; hash&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;key&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 1: Safe hash access&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;config &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; { &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;database&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; { &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;host&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;localhost&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;port&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5432&lt;/span&gt; } }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;host &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; config&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;dig(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;database&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;host&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# &amp;#34;localhost&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;timeout &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; config&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;dig(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;database&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;timeout&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# nil&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;timeout &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;||=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;30&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# 30&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 2: Building with defaults&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;settings &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; {}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;defaults &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; { &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;theme&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;dark&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;lang&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;en&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;result &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; defaults&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;merge(settings)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;result&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;fetch(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;theme&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# &amp;#34;dark&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/ruby/no-method-error/"&gt;NoMethodError&lt;/a&gt; — undefined method for object&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/ruby/typeerror-ruby/"&gt;TypeError&lt;/a&gt; — wrong object type for an operation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/ruby/index-error/"&gt;IndexError&lt;/a&gt; — index out of range in array&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>Can't use string as HASH</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/perl/reference-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/perl/reference-error/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;Can't use string as HASH reference&lt;/code&gt; error is raised when you try to dereference a scalar value as a hash reference, but the value is actually a string or other non-reference type. This commonly happens with incorrect data structures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Treating string as hash reference&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wrong data structure assumptions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Missing reference creation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Incorrect dereferencing syntax&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-perl" data-lang="perl"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# WRONG: Using string as hash&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;my&lt;/span&gt; $str &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;print&lt;/span&gt; $str&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;{key}; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Can&amp;#39;t use string as HASH reference&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# CORRECT: Create hash reference&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;my&lt;/span&gt; $hash &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; { key &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;value&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; };
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;print&lt;/span&gt; $hash&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;{key};
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-perl" data-lang="perl"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# WRONG: Wrong dereferencing&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;my&lt;/span&gt; @arr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;print&lt;/span&gt; $arr&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;{&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;}; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Can&amp;#39;t use array as HASH&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# CORRECT: Use correct dereferencing&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;my&lt;/span&gt; @arr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;print&lt;/span&gt; $arr[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# or&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;print&lt;/span&gt; $arr&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-perl" data-lang="perl"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 1: String as hash&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;my&lt;/span&gt; $data &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;not a hash&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;print&lt;/span&gt; $data&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;{name}; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Can&amp;#39;t use string as HASH reference&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 2: Array as hash&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;my&lt;/span&gt; @list &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;print&lt;/span&gt; $list&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;{key}; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Can&amp;#39;t use array as HASH reference&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 3: Undefined reference&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;my&lt;/span&gt; $ref;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;print&lt;/span&gt; $ref&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;{key}; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Can&amp;#39;t use undefined value as HASH reference&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/perl/glob-error"&gt;Glob failed&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/perl/die-error"&gt;die error&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>